		<title>
		By: Aaron		</title>
		<link>https://www.ultrasaurus.com/2009/12/creating-a-custom-rake-task/#comment-1490</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Aaron]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2013 21:46:21 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.ultrasaurus.com/?p=2236#comment-1490</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[&lt;p&gt;The latest version of Heroku add &quot;run&quot; to the command. Therefore:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;%&#062; heroku run rake:db:migrate&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;instead of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;%&#062; heroku rake:db:migrate&lt;/p&gt;
]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The latest version of Heroku add &#8220;run&#8221; to the command. Therefore:</p>
<p>%&gt; heroku run rake:db:migrate</p>
<p>instead of:</p>
<p>%&gt; heroku rake:db:migrate</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
