					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ultrasaurus.com/2009/12/creating-a-custom-rake-task/#comment-643&quot;&gt;Aravind&lt;/a&gt;.

:task_name =&#062; :environment will load the Rails environment, which will allow you to access things like your ActiveRecord models or Rails config.  Without that you can just run pure Ruby code.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://www.ultrasaurus.com/2009/12/creating-a-custom-rake-task/#comment-643">Aravind</a>.</p>
<p>:task_name =&gt; :environment will load the Rails environment, which will allow you to access things like your ActiveRecord models or Rails config.  Without that you can just run pure Ruby code.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
